1. *Slaba* ekonomija utiče na standard života ljudi. (*Weak* economy affects the standard of living of people.)
2. Njegovo znanje je *slabo* u odnosu na ostale kolege. (His knowledge is *weak* compared to other colleagues.)
3. Ova biljka zahteva *slabo* zalivanje. (This plant requires *little* watering.)
4. *Slab* vetar neće pokrenuti list na drvetu. (*Weak* wind won't move a leaf on the tree.)
5. Ona je *slaba* na slatkiše. (She is *weak* when it comes to sweets.)
6. *Slabašan* glas nije dovoljan za javni nastup. (*Weak* voice is not enough for public speaking.)
7. Njihova veza je bila *slaba* i brzo se raspala. (Their relationship was *weak* and quickly fell apart.)
8. *Slaba* tačka u ovom planu je nedostatak finansijskih resursa. (*Weak* point in this plan is the lack of financial resources.)
9. Kada je bolestan, njegov apetit je *slab*. (When he's sick, his appetite is *poor*.)
10. Njegova sposobnost da pravi odluke je *slaba*. (His ability to make decisions is *weak*.)